e probably a nickname for someone who paid that amount in rent."]}]},{"name":"Alexander","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin form of the Greek name <i>Alexandros</i>, from <i>alexein</i> ‘to defend’ + <i>anēr</i> ‘man, warrior’ (genitive <i>andros</i>). The name became extremely popular in the post-classical period, and was borne by several individuals in the New Testament and some early Christian saints. Its use as a common given name throughout Europe, however, derives largely from the fame of  Alexander the Great , King of Macedon (  356–323  bc  ), around whom a large body of popular legend grew up in late antiquity, much of which came to be embodied in the medieval ‘Alexander romances’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alexander Stirling was born in 1150, in Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Alexander Stirling. He died in 1244, at the age of 94."},"et":{"1150–1244":"1150–1244","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1190":"1190","1244":"1244","1155":"1155","1150":"1150","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1150–1244":"1150–1244","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1244":"1244","1155":"1155","1150":"1150","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1150–1244":"1150–1244","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1190–Female":"1190–Décédée","1190":"1190","1244":"1244","1155":"1155","1150":"1150","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Écosse","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Alexander Stirling est né en 1150, à Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Écosse. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs. Alexander Stirling. Il est décédé en 1244, à l’âge de 94 ans."},"de":{"1150–